Tips for connecting wifi through command line on ubuntu terminal or ssh

example : wap security type , test1 is SSID  KEY is 1234567890.

/usr/share/checkbox/scripts/create_connection test1 --security=wap --key=1234567890

this will create connection on /etc/NetwrkManager/system-connections/test1

example : wap security type , test1 is SSID  KEY is 1234567890.

/usr/share/checkbox/scripts/create_connection test1 --security=wep --key=1234567890
sed -i 's/wep-key=/wep-key0=/g' /etc/NetworkManager/system-connections/test1 


sparky sbc onboard ethernet: by default configured on dhcp , wired ethernet connect to router 

with the use of "Advanced IP scanner" windows application can identify the IP address of the board.

 

